ROS Setup Guide

Description

This is a guide on how to setup ROS, Jackal bot, and use BARN data set on Ubuntu 20.04.

Installing ROS

Please refer to this link: ROS Official Install Guide.

Installing Jackal

Create a workspace and clone sources

mkdir -p jackal_ws/src; cd jackal_ws/src; catkin_init_workspace
git clone https://github.com/jackal/jackal.git
git clone https://github.com/jackal/jackal_simulator.git
git clone https://github.com/jackal/jackal_desktop.git
git clone https://github.com/ros-visualization/interactive_marker_twist_server.git
cd ..

Install dependencies with rosdep :

rosdep install --from-paths . --ignore-src --rosdistro=noetic

Build and source

catkin_make
source devel/setup.bash

Start simulation :

In terminal :

roslaunch jackal_gazebo jackal_world.launch config:=front_laser gui:=true

You should see a window popping up with a robot on a map like this.

If you are a lazy person

Each time before you run roslaunch jackal_gazebo jackal_world.launch config:=front_laser gui:=true, you’ll need to setup the environment. There is a workaround you can do to let it automatically set up.

If you use bash:

echo 'source <path to your jackal_ws>/devel/setup.bash' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

If you use zsh:

echo 'source <path to your jackal_ws>/devel/setup.zsh' >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc

Teleoperation

My teleoperation setup was done with a bluetooth Xbox One controller. There is a little configuration that needs to be done before we can teleoperate. Using other controllers should be okay.

Make sure Bluetooth controller is working

Pair the Xbox controller with the laptop. If the pairing is successful, try

sudo echo /dev/input/js0

Twist the joystick on your controller, and you should see the terminal is printing non-sense right now. If not, there might be a problem with controller pairing.

If you really want to see what you get from the joystick:

sudo apt install jstest
jstest /dev/input/js0

Then you should the what you pressed on the controller in a human-friendly way.

Modify teleop configuration

First cd to the jackal_ws folder, then

cd src/jackal/jackal_control/

If you have vscode installed

code .

Delete everything and paste following configuration into launch/teleop.launch:

<launch>
  <arg name="joy_dev" default="/dev/input/js0" />
  <arg name="joystick" default="true" />
  <!--
  <group ns="bluetooth_teleop" if="$(arg joystick)">
        
    <group unless="$(optenv JACKAL_PS3 0)" >
      <rosparam command="load" file="$(find jackal_control)/config/teleop_ps4.yaml" />
      <param name="joy_node/dev" value="$(arg joy_dev)" />
    </group>

    <group if="$(optenv JACKAL_PS3 0)" >
      <rosparam command="load" file="$(find jackal_control)/config/teleop_ps3.yaml" />
      <param name="joy_node/dev" value="$(arg joy_dev)" />
    </group>

  </group>
  -->
  <!-- <rosparam command="load" file="$(find jackal_control)/config/teleop_ps4.yaml" />
      <param name="joy_node/dev" value="$(arg joy_dev)" /> -->
  <rosparam command="load" file="$(find jackal_control)/config/teleop_xone.yaml" />
  <param name="joy_node/dev" value="$(arg joy_dev)" />
  <node pkg="joy" type="joy_node" name="joy_node" />

  <node pkg="teleop_twist_joy" type="teleop_node" name="teleop_twist_joy" />


  <node pkg="interactive_marker_twist_server" type="marker_server" name="twist_marker_server">
    <param name="link_name" value="base_link" />
  </node>
</launch>

Then in config folder, create teleop_xone.yaml and paste the following configuration:

# Teleop configuration for Xbox One joystick using the x-pad configuration.
teleop_twist_joy:
  axis_linear: 1
  scale_linear: 0.4
  scale_linear_turbo: 2.0
  axis_angular: 0
  scale_angular: 1.4
  enable_button: 0
  enable_turbo_button: 1
joy_node:
  deadzone: 0.1
  autorepeat_rate: 20

Restart Gazebo

Stop gazebo, and relaunch with this command

roslaunch jackal_gazebo jackal_world.launch config:=front_laser gui:=true

You should be able to teleoperate the Jackal bot with the controller.

You need to hold A while moving the joystick to control the bot. That’s how it works!

If you want it to move faster, hold B instead of A!

Load world from BARN dataset

If you want to load a world from BARN dataset, use the command:

roslaunch jackal_gazebo jackal_world.launch config:=front_laser gui:=true world_name:=<the absolute path of the world that you want to load from BARN>

You can see due to the default position from the launch file, the robot was put on a wall when placed into the world, and it eventually flipped. To fix this, go to <place where jackal_ws is>/src/jackal_simulator/jackal_gazebo/launch and change line 32 and 33 of jackal_world.launch to:

    <arg name="x" value="-1" />
    <arg name="y" value="1" />

Then use the original command to run again. You should see something like this:
